UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Ferrari Rep/Figaro/3 Tractors: Derek is on the road to pick up a funky little Nissan Figaro and a sublime Ferrari 250 GT tribute car, and Paul gets to try out his spanking new Scania T Cab. S9 Ep7

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Abandoned Engineering
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Rock and Ruin: Exploring traces of a mass deception hidden at Ponte Dirillo in Italy, as well as a once-lavish theatre in Ohio and an ancient city with a poisonous secret. S10 Ep7

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Great American Railroad Journeys
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Reno To The Napa Valley: Michael Portillo travels from Reno, Nevada to California's Napa County, taking to the skies over the Sierra Nevada mountain range. S3 Ep1

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Secret Nazi Bases
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Dag Bromberg: A City in the Forest: As the Red Army approached a forest in Poland toward the end of the war, they stumbled upon a complex containing more than 1,000 structures across 25sqkm. S1 Ep5

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: The Monster and the Butcher: 'The Butcher of Lyon' and 'Ivan the Terrible' - join the hunt for Gestapo head Klaus Barbie and death camp guard Ivan Grozny, which lasted into the 1980s. S1 Ep11

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Baddesley Clinton 2: The team value more rarities at Baddesley Clinton, near Solihull, including a rare silver box and a painting entitled The Nudist Colony's Annual Dinner Dance. S39 Ep9

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Antiques Roadshow
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Golden Age of Travel Special: Fiona Bruce presents from on board the Flying Scotsman during a journey across Cumbria and Yorkshire, with passengers sharing stories from the history of travel. S39 Ep10

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Cortina 2000E/Daimler V250: Nothing screams 1970s more than a Mk3 Ford Cortina 2000E. Derek Mathewson heads to Brigg to value a 1974 example with classic Coke bottle styling and a Pinto engine. S4 Ep4
